This simple implementation allows users to select one or more files for upload and enter a path for scanning images; both invoke functions that call your FastAPI backend endpoints.

For a more advanced scenario, you may want to build a more sophisticated UI/UX involving progress feedback for uploads, confirmation messages, error handling for failed requests, and avoiding direct browser interaction with file systems. Depending on what's supported by the browsers and the file input facilities they offer, you may need to use libraries or other methods to handle directory uploads.

