If you need to pass just the file path as a string, you can take advantage of a text input field where users can paste or type the path to their local files or directories. However, do note that due to security reasons, modern web browsers do not provide the full path to the selected file in file dialogs, and they also generally prevent web content from directly accessing the local filesystem. If your server has access to the same filesystem as the client, you could use a text input to capture the path.

