If you have a state in React defined as `documentTitle` and set up with `useState`, you can access its value directly within your component, including in any functions that are part of that component. For example:

```jsx
const [documentTitle, setDocumentTitle] = useState("");

const sendPostRequest = async () => {
    try {
        const response = await axios.post('your-api-endpoint', {
            // You can directly use documentTitle in your Axios request payload
            title: documentTitle
        });
