The `onChange` event handler for the `Input` component from Ant Design does not provide the value directly but instead provides an event object. To get the value of the input, you need to access the `value` property on the `target` of the event object.

Here's the correct way to handle the `onChange` event for the `Input` component in Ant Design:

```jsx
<Input
  id="inputTitleBox"
  value={documentTitle}
  placeholder="Document Title"
  onChange={(e) => {
    setDocumentTitle(e.target.value);
  }}
/>
```

When the input value changes, `e.target.value` will provide the current value of the input, which you can then use to update the `documentTitle` state with `setDocumentTitle`.

So your corrected component would look something like this:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Input } from 'antd';

const YourComponent = () => {
  const [documentTitle, setDocumentTitle] = useState("");

